We recommended and management agreed that (a) the LCPC/CCWPC submit the reports and documents  required under DILG MC 	No. 2008-126 and DILG MC No. 2012-120, respectively; 

(b) the CSWD and City Budget Officer adhere with the provisions of RA 9344 on the required allocation of the amount equivalent to 1% of IRA for the purpose; and 
(c) conduct timely planning and implementation of the programs, projects and activities for the child protection and development to efficiently deliver the services to the intended beneficiaries.

For infrastructure projects, we have recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
Bids and Awards Committee to consider bidders  as eligible only when the SLCC are supported with either photocopies of Certificates of Final Acceptance (CFA) or a final rating of at least Satisfactory in the Constructors Performance Evaluation Sytem (CPES);
Municipal Engineer and Inspectorate Team to conduct inspection of completed projects after the one year defects liability period;
Municipal Engineer require the Contractor prior to issuance of CFA posting of warranty security in any acceptable form; and
BAC and Municipal Engineer to establish a system and maintain records on specific warranty periods and security for each procurement of civil works.

We recommended to management that contractors be responsible in rectifying the defects. We further recommend that in order to prevent the occurrence of similar deficiencies, the following actions be taken into consideration in the implementation of all ADM/infrastructure projects:
Conduct close monitoring of the implementation of Quality Control and ensure that all required tests are conducted;
Require the contractor’s deployment of a full-time supervision team as provided in the contract as well as full-time supervision by the resident engineer;
Ensure that all necessary documentations such as progress reports, quality control reports, weather monitoring chart, construction schedule, approved work requests/ pouring permits, site instructions, logbooks, as-tasked plans and approved variation order/time extensions (if any) are prepared and filed accordingly;
Advise the contractor to strictly comply with the provisions of RA 9184 on the warranty of infrastructure projects.

